From: Kari.Hurtta@Helsinki.FI (Kari E. Hurtta)
Crossposted-To: comp.os.linux.help
Subject: Re: USERS CAN DELETE ROOT  FILES!!
Date: 20 Nov 1993 21:42:38 GMT

(And I am again commenting myself).

Perhaps that helps about semantic of protection field: 
Think directory as file which have two things - file name
and pointer to file. 

Directory's protection field protect that content.
File's protection field protect that content which are in end of that pointer.
So if you want remove file you need only modify content of directory
which is protected by directory's protection field - you need not go
through that pointer.

(And this is metaphor! So do not complaing that if I don't mention all 
 details how this is really implemented in unixes.)

--
- K E H                                      /  Elämä on monimutkaista
  Kari.Hurtta@Helsinki.FI

